f everything, are already very impatient, because everyone has only one single aim in view, to leave the country which once was hell for him."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "6509.492","u": "And where do they want to go?"},    {"who": "Helen Tichauer", "start": "6511.492","u": "Go? They have one aim. Out of Europe. In part . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "6517.408","u": "Are there many who want to go to Palestine?"},    {"who": "Helen Tichauer", "start": "6519.378","u": "Of course. There are people, young . . . mainly youth, who want to readjust, want to learn, and who [would] feel at home, let us say, in a national Jewish State. Mostly the youth."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "6537.553","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Helen Tichauer", "start": "6538.348","u": "There is also a part of Jews who have a relative in America and have lost their whole European family and are assembling now the rest of such a family who want to spend their life with them. Also with the intention to learn near them a trade, to re-adjust, free . . . as free workers . . . free workers . . . in an American state [country], so as to live . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "6571.183","u": "Tell me, do you have any contacts with the Germans around here?"},    {"who": "Helen Tichauer", "start": "6576.737","u": "[Hesitantly] Contact with the Germans? No. Actually no, because the Germans of Upper Bavaria have no desire [interest] to establish a contact with us. They have no intention whatsoever to feel in some way guilty, although we know exactly that Upper Bavaria has very few people, [they] have very few relatives who were [? were not?] in [belonged to] the Nazi Party. Upper Bavaria was the center of Party conventions. We have Nurenburg. We have Munich."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "6614.437","u": "That is they were all in the Party?"},    {"who": "Helen Tichauer", "start": "6616.106","u": "To a large extent. And I can say only one thing. The German population in other lands [states] of Germany behaves completely different."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "6629.763","u": "Better?"},    {"who": "Helen Tichauer", "start": "6630.618","u": "Better than the Upper Bavarian [?] population. And precisely for that reason one cannot demand from our people that we should have any sympathy . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "6642.742","u": "[Two words not clear.]"},    {"who": "Helen Tichauer", "start": "6643.628","u": ". . . or should establish any contact with those people. We understand. There are children, innocent German children, who are as innocent as were our children, who also [the following words are not clear due to the affective tone of voice] who also perished [?] in multitudes. And . . . even have composed a song about it. All hatred must be brought about [cultivated], but we experience no hatred whatsoever. But we feel that we are actually still hated. Still hated!"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "6678.361","u": "Now, and you yourself, where do you want to go?"},    {"who": "Helen Tichauer", "start": "6681.686","u": "I myself [here follows a brief silence on a wire, 4 to 5 seconds, possibly due to failure of equipment] . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "6686.728","u": "With your husband?"},    {"who": "Helen Tichauer", "start": "6687.764","u": "By myself. Not with my husband, who actually comes from [is originally from ]Berlin, [and] is a German Jew, but considers himself now actually stateless. I presume, had I not found this man, I should have liked to live in Czechoslovakia, would have liked to live there very much, because I felt there always very well [I used to be always very happy there]. I know that nation. I feel a bond with Czechoslovakia."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "6716.111","u": "Otherwise you want to go to South America."},    {"who": "Helen Tichauer", "start": "6718.108","u": "Otherwise [a few words not clear]. Otherwise . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "6719.102","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Helen Tichauer", "start": "6719.674","u": "For the reason that my husband has the rest of his family in South America. In Germany we shall never feel well. In this country there is nothing [?] for us . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "6732.174","u": "[In English] We regret we have to finish this interview. The automobile is waiting. This concludes Spool 150."}        ]
    }
_jsready = true;
var return_val;
switch (String(type)){
        case "transcription":
        return_val = transcription.interview;
        break;
            case "english_translation":
        return_val = english_translation.interview;
        break;
    }
return return_val;
}
function js_ready(){
    return _jsready;
}
